{
  "stem": "27747.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in those years, my brother already encouraged my mother to sell the business and the house and come to Israel because he had refugees from Germany, and they were scared and worried, and he related to her that the times are coming.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That-- he was always a pessimist, but he was right this time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said, come, take Paula and take Leah and Sonia and come to-- to Israel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my mother was a little bit on the stubborn side and she said, am I going to go and-- and-- and be dependent on the children?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, make a living?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I can't make a living there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they remained in the town of Hoszcza.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the war between-- between '36 and '39, there was an exceptional influx of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "German people that lived in our areas were taught that they were the ones that showed the Germans where to bomb.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not the villages, but the middle of the town of Hoszcza.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In 1939, you know, with the blitzkrieg, in no time, Poland lost the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Russian occupied in 1941, made a pact with Hitler, and occupied our town of Hoszcza.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the eastern part up to the Hoszcza, up to Warsaw was, belonged to-- to the-- to the Soviet Union, and the German had the other western part of Poland-- south, west, and north.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Soviets, when they came during the war, since it was a pact, they had no fighting, so it was a peaceful exchange.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Soviets immediately nationalized all the homes of the better-to-do people, and they--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was in '41.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Up until '39.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in gymnasium at that time, and I returned from the gymnasium of Rowne.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Rowne, right.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
